{"title":"Tour of Britain 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and all you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-route-riders-live-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know","date":1724779092000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-route-riders-live-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\">Tour of Britain 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and all you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-of-britain\" target=\"_blank\">Tour of Britain</a> 2024 is not far away. It was only last autumn when <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/wout-van-aert/\" target=\"_blank\">Wout van Aert </a>took the overall title after a week of domination alongside Jumbo-Visma teammate Olav Kooij. This September, the Tour of Britain returns for its 20th edition.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 event begins in Kelso in the Scottish Borders on Tuesday 3rd September and finishes in Felixstowe, Suffolk on Sunday 8th September. The six-day race will pass through the Scottish Borders, North Yorkshire, Sheffield, Northamptonshire and East Anglia throughout the week of racing. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The reigning champion Van Aert will not be in attendance this year. The Olympic champion <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> is expected to be on the startline in Kelso. He will be joined by teammate Julian Alaphilippe and fellow Olympian <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tom-pidcock\" target=\"_blank\">Tom Pidcock</a> of Ineos Grenadiers. Four UCI WorldTour teams will compete in the 2024 Tour of Britain.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclists ride up hill in shadow of trees\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-047-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dates:</strong> Tuesday 3rd to Sunday 8th September 2024<br /><strong>Start:</strong> Kelso, Scotland<br /><strong>Finish:</strong> Felixstowe, England<br /><strong>UK television coverage:</strong> ITV4, Eurosport, Discovery+<br /><strong>Television coverage elsewhere:</strong> Eurosport (Europe, Asia and Oceania), Discovery+ (Europe, Asia, Oceania and North America), L’Équipe (France), RTVC (Colombia), Starzplay (North Africa), SuperSport (Sub-Saharan Africa)</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-women-2024-photos\">The best photos from the Tour of Britain Women 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/lincoln-gp-2024-gallery\">Lincoln GP gallery: Photos from Britain’s Tour of Flanders</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-cycling-plan-2024\">What is British Cycling’s plan for the future of road racing in the UK? </a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-2023\">The best photos from the Tour of Britain 2023</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024 route</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"three cyclists ride by crowd\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-040-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Matt Grayson</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 edition of the Tour of Britain will be six stages long. This means this year’s race will be the shortest since 2007 (with the exception of the 2022 race, which was abandoned early due to the death of Queen Elizabeth II). The total length of the race is 936.5km.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour will visit England and Scotland, omitting Wales, which held half of the racing at the recent<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-women-2024-photos\" target=\"_blank\"> Tour of Britain Women</a> in June. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There will be no time-trial involved<em>,</em> neither will the race close out with a city-centre stage in Manchester, London or Glasgow. The race will, however, include a cobbled finish, steep kickers and wind-exposed roads. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024 stage-by-stage preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Tuesday 3rd September, Kelso – Kelso</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage1_Route_Map_3.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After a year’s hiatus from the men’s race, Scotland returns to the Tour of Britain <em>parcours</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"308\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile-970x308.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile-970x308.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile-300x95.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile-768x244.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile-750x238.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-1-profile.png 1108w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The race will begin in Kelso, the hometown of<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-riders-tour-de-france\"> </a><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/british-riders-tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">DSM-Firmenich-PostNL rider Oscar Onley</a>. There’s 1,855m of altitude gain on offer on Stage 1’s profile, which loops around Galashiels, Coldstream and Kelso. After a final lap around Galashiels up Scott’s View and Dingleton, the peloton will return to Kelso with an arrival in the cobbled town square.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, Jayco-AlUla have had success under their previous monikers in Kelso. Caleb Ewan won in the town in 2017 and Matteo Trentin took a win here in 2019.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Wednesday 4th September, Darlington – Redcar</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage2_v3_1.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 2 heads into England with a start in Darlington. The stage will traverse the Tees Valley and North Yorkshire Moors during a 150km-long stage along the 2,216m of elevation of offer.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"312\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile-970x312.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile-970x312.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile-300x96.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile-768x247.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile-750x241.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-2-profile.png 1114w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The stage will begin its razor tooth profile at the halfway marker at Ugglebarnby Moor. This short and steep climb at an average of 9% will set the tone for the second half of the stage. Raw Pasture Bank, Lythe Bank and Saltburn Bank will be loaded into the final 80km. The climb up to Saltburn will be familiar to British riders who have tackled the ascent during the National Championships over the past two years.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The stage will end in the steelmaking town of Redcar. The finishing approach has been confirmed by race organisers to take place along the seafront of the North Yorkshire town.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Thursday 5th September, Sheffield – Barnsley</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage3_Route_Map.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The third stage of racing kicks off in the South Yorkshire city of Sheffield. The hometown of the Arctic Monkeys, Adam Blythe and Michael Palin, Sheffield has hosted the Tour of Britain and the Tour de France in the past two decades. This will be Sheffield’s big comeback to cycling, as the city hasn’t hosted a stage of Britain’s top stage race since 2006.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"306\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile-970x306.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile-970x306.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile-300x94.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile-768x242.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile-750x236.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-3-profile.png 1108w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 3 will be an undulating stage through the Peak District and Moors as the race winds its way around South Yorkshire. The final 20km of the day will prove pivotal with a long drag to Wentworth Castle. After that, a sharp climb at Hound Hill (1.4km at 5.6%) will sharpen the back end of this stage. The final kilometre into Barnsley will also be an uphill drag along the Old Mill Lane. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Friday 6th September, Derby – Newark-on-Trent</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/ToBM_2024_Stage4_Route_Map.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The stage will begin in Derby by the city’s Derby Arena, home to one of the UK’s few indoor velodromes. The track is home to the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/beginning-with-the-best-an-introduction-to-track-cycling-with-huub-wattbike\" target=\"_blank\">Huub-Watt Bike</a> team who colloquially refer to the Midlands city as Derbados. This will be the first stage to pass through Derbyshire since 2015.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile-970x305.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile-970x305.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile-300x94.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile-768x241.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile-750x236.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-4-profile.png 1110w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 4 will be flat with no intermediate climbs on the menu. The approach to the line in Newark-on-Trent will also be flat and straightforward. This stage should be an all-out sprint in the East Midlands town of Newark. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Saturday 7th September, Northampton – Northampton</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_3-6_v12_1.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 5, the penultimate stage, will both start and finish in Northampton. The town will make its men’s Tour of Britain debut this year. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"306\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile-970x306.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile-970x306.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile-300x94.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile-768x242.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile-750x236.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-5-profile.png 1108w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The route around West Northamptonshire is flat and untesting. The two categorised climbs of Bullshill and Newnham Hill are unremarkable in terms of the stage profile. They will not cause any big splits in the group with neither of them lasting more than 1km in length.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The approach to the line could be hectic after such a flat day. The arrival to the line is also at a slight false flat so that could open up the race for some outsiders.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Sunday 8th September, Lowestoft – Felixstowe</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/BC_ToBM_2024_Overview_Maps_Stages_6.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, the race will travel a couple of hours down the road to Suffolk for the closing stage of the 2024 Tour of Britain. The day begins in Lowestoft, the most easterly town in the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"304\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile-970x304.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile-970x304.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile-300x94.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile-768x241.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile-750x235.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/TOB-24-Stage-6-profile.png 1110w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The route then heads inland for an intermediate sprint within the opening handful of kilometres. With bonus seconds available, these could be tightly contested on the final day of racing. The race then skirts southwards close to the Suffolk coastline. There’s another intermediate sprint in Aldeburgh before a chaotic approach to the line in Felixstowe.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The arrival will be the same as Stage 5 from last year’s Tour of Britain won by Wout van Aert. Given the flat terrain of Suffolk, expect another bunch gallop to the line. Beware of the East Anglian wind, there is a real chance that last-minute echelons could affect the sixth and final stage.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024: How to watch</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"three cyclists race by crowd in village\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-032-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Matt Grayson</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Across Europe, the Tour of Britain will be broadcast live on Discovery+. The basic package for <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> costs £6.99 per month, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. With so much cycling in early September, the Tour of Britain will not be broadcast live on Eurosport 1. There will be highlights packages instead.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For UK viewers, the Tour of Britain will be broadcast on free-to-air channel ITV4. The stages will be shown live and highlights are scheduled each night on ITV4 at 8pm BST. The racing will be streamed via ITV’s streaming site ITVX.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour of Britain will be broadcast live through British Cycling’s YouTube channel much like during <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-tour-of-britain-women\" target=\"_blank\">the Tour of Britain Women earlier this year</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs from £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024 broadcast times</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclists on road above a beach\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-053-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Tuesday 3rd September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:15-16:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Wednesday 4th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Thursday 5th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+ </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Friday 6th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Saturday 8th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+  </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4</strong>: TBC</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Sunday 9th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4:</strong> TBC</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclists race to line\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-028-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=45&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n            